# Repository Browsers

-   [darcsden](http://hub.darcs.net) - a Darcs hosting website you can
    install on your servers
-   [Darcsweb](http://blitiri.com.ar/p/darcsweb/) - A web-based repo
    browser.
    ([example](http://www.divineinvasion.net/darcsweb/darcsweb.cgi))
-   [patch-tag](http://blog.patch-tag.com/2010/07/21/patch-tag-lessons-learned-and-announcing-open-source/)
    -a Darcs hosting website
    ([example](http://allmydata.org/trac/darcs-2/browser))
-   [FusionForge](http://www.fusionforge.org/) 5.0 (formerly GForge)
    supports Darcs via a plugin
-   [dawb](http://rampa.sk/static/dawb.html) - is simple web-based
    changes browser (with RSS support)

# User Interface

-   [meld](http://meld.sourceforge.net/), a graphical diff viewer,
    handles darcs repositories: just type "meld ." inside of a darcs
    repo to see the unrecorded changes (no longer works as of Meld 3.15
    but we're working on reintroducing darcs support)
-   [diffuse](http://diffuse.sourceforge.net/), a graphical diff viewer,
    handles darcs repositories: just type "diffuse -m" inside of a darcs
    repo to see the unrecorded changes
-   [Darcs support for the Emacs text editor](RelatedSoftware/Emacs)
-   [darcs.vim](http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=1683) - basic Darcs support for vim
-   [Shell Completions](RelatedSoftware/ShellCompletion) for bash, zsh,
    tcsh and emacs.
-   [Lispworks](http://www.kantz.com/jason/programs/vc/vc-for-lw.html)
    - Version Control for Lispworks, allows darcs use from the Lispworks
    IDE
-   [Gnus](RelatedSoftware/Gnus) - A small recipe for Gnus to apply
    patches from the mail client.
-   [commit-patch](http://porkrind.org/commit-patch) - Commit a patch
    file to a darcs, hg or cvs repo. Includes convenient emacs hooks.
-   From [Ideas/GraphicalInterface#See also](Ideas/GraphicalInterface#see-also):
    -   <http://www.datafed.net/darcs/> (TortoiseDarcs, Windows GUI for Darcs)
    -   [EclipseDarcs](http://eclipsedarcs.sourceforge.net/) (last version:
        4.1, March 2008). See also
         <http://cohatoe.blogspot.com/search/label/eclipsedarcs>
        and
        <http://web.archive.org/web/20071012050446/eclipsedarcs.org/doku.php?id=eclipsedarcs>

