# Plugins

-   [musdex](http://lists.osuosl.org/pipermail/darcs-users/2010-March/023171.html)
    - a pre and posthook that enables darcs to version compressed files,
    typically .odt or .docx files.

# Other

-   [Gitit](http://gitit.net) a wiki engine that can use darcs as backend.
-   [DarcsWatch](http://darcswatch.nomeata.de/) tracks patches submitted
    to projects and their status. It can be used to track personal
    submissions or watch a community mailing list.
-   [darcsver](http://pypi.python.org/pypi/darcsver/) - generate a
    version number from darcs history
-   [darcs-mirror](http://ydirson.free.fr/soft/graph-includes/darcs-mirror),
    a small script to push using FTP (requires lftp) to a web-site.
    Useful when FTP is the only write access to your public web pages.
-   [Trac integration](RelatedSoftware/Trac) - Instructions on how to
    set up a trac server, thus getting a sourceforge like environment
-   [darcs-server](http://www.equational.org/darcs-server/) - An
    authenticating push / pull protocol for darcs.
-   [buildbot](http://buildbot.sourceforge.net/) can track and build
    projects from darcs repositories.
-   [darcs-reannotate](RelatedSoftware/DarcsReannotate) : a small
    program that will reformat "darcs annotate" to make it easier to
    read (only useful for darcs 2.5.x or older).

